{{Maldives-bio-stub}}

'''Ilham Ahmed''' is a Maldivian politician who is the current [[Member of Parliament|MP]] for [[Dhangethi]] Constituency in the [[People's Majlis]], former [[Member of Parliament|MP]] for [[Gemanafushi]] Constituency in the [[People's Majlis]] and the Former President of [[Football Association of Maldives]].<ref>http://www.haveeru.com.mv/sports/47064</ref> Ilham was one of the Vice Presidents of [[Jumhooree Party]] and was formerly one of the two Vice Presidents of [[Progressive Party of Maldives]] elected by the first congress of the party.<ref>http://sun.mv/english/8851</ref> A native of [[Gemanafushi]] in [[Huvadhu Atoll]], Ilham's family roots can be traced back to [[Fuvahmulah]] and [[Addu Atoll]] as well. Due to the increased oppression of the Maldivian government, Ilham resigned from PPM on 9th July 2017 becoming an Independent member. 
<ref>http://liyuntherin.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=283</ref><ref>http://liyuntherin.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=243</ref>

