{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}} {{Distinguish|text=the Syrian-Kurdish politician, [[√élham Ehmed]], whose name is often rendered as √élham Ahmed}} '''Ilham Ahmed''' is a Maldivian politician who is the current [[Member of Parliament|MP]] for [[Dhangethi]] Constituency in the [[People's Majlis]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ilham Ahmed - People's Majlis of Maldives |url=https://majlis.gov.mv/en/18-parliament/members/38 |access-date=2022-04-20 |website=majlis.gov.mv}}</ref> He is former [[Member of Parliament|MP]] for [[Gemanafushi]] Constituency in the [[People's Majlis]] and the Former President of [[Football Association of Maldives]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.haveeru.com.mv/sports/47064 |title=Archived copy |access-date=29 March 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130130011655/http://www.haveeru.com.mv/sports/47064 |archive-date=30 January 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Ilham was one of the Vice Presidents of [[Jumhooree Party]] and was formerly one of the two Vice Presidents of [[Progressive Party of Maldives]] elected by the first congress of the party.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.sun.mv/8851|title=Adheeb and Ilham elected as vice presidents of PPM|website=SunOnline International}}</ref> A native of [[Gemanafushi]] in [[Huvadhu Atoll]], Ilham's family roots can be traced back to [[Fuvahmulah]] and [[Addu Atoll]] as well. Due to the increased oppression of the Maldivian government, Ilham resigned from PPM on 9 July 2017 becoming an Independent member.<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|url=http://liyuntherin.org/|title=ﬁäﬁ™ﬁÉﬁ¶ﬁåﬁ¶ﬁâﬁ¶ ﬁûﬁ¶ﬁäﬁ∞ﬁôﬁß -|website=liyuntherin.org}}</ref>
